"Well, really, when I consider that she has turned her back--I will not say upon me, but upon so
much that many have aspired to without success--I can hardly explain it in any other fashion."

"Well, certainly that is also a conceivable hypothesis," said Holmes, smiling. "And now, Lord St.
Simon, I think that I have nearly all my data. May I ask whether you were seated at the breakfast-
table so that you could see out of the window?"